It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. It's the last room in the house that was only given simple decoration.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and the stove. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Customize a wardrobe.
We usually start by drawing a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
Found a few dead birds behind the flue, all of them dried out :(
Prepare to welcome the plasterer next week
Very satisfied with the small niche next to it
Install the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet🙈)
Ha ha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the cute little vent added to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Sweep has installed the chimney cover and the chimney cap. Those ravens that like to build nests in the chimney should be safer now 🪺
The plasterer has finished. We will lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork underlay has been laid, and we even made a attachment for the vacuum cleaner using toilet paper rolls to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared and is ready to be laid. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow because, in order to seamlessly connect with the hallway (which is also having floorboards laid), I had to do some cutting around the door frame, which was quite laborious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me all along
Finally finished, but it's a mess! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. Tonight I can finally sleep well!
The corridor floor and skirting board are still to be done. The renovation workers won't come for a month, so we can only make do for now, with just bare plasterboard in the room.
DIY a bit in the evening, cutting off part of the bottom of the door frame with a saw and chisel, so the floor can be perfectly laid underneath.
The cork underlay in the corridor is also laid.
We also laid the corridor floor yesterday! I got up at 5 in the morning today to go to Heathrow Airport and pick up package 1, then had a nap, and now I can finally start installing the skirting board in the corridor. Once the adhesive dries, I'll fill the gaps.
